# GitHub Linguist overrides
#
# VL (.vl) is not a registered Linguist language, so GitHub would not
# syntax-highlight .vl files at all without an override.  TypeScript is the
# closest grammar: VL shares its `function`/`let`/`const`/`type` keywords,
# generic angle-bracket syntax `<T>`, union `A | B`, optional-chain `?.`,
# null-coalesce `??`, `//`/`///` comments, `"…"` strings, `'x'` char
# literals, `0x`/`0b`/`0o` numeric prefixes with `_` digit-separators, and
# `is`-narrowing that reads like a TS type predicate.  No other supported
# Linguist language (Swift `func`, Rust `fn`, Go no-angle-generics, Kotlin
# different object syntax) matches the token set this closely.
#
# Side-effect: Linguist will also count .vl lines as "TypeScript" in the
# repo language-statistics bar.  The `linguist-detectable=false` line below
# suppresses that: .vl files will still be highlighted as TypeScript, but
# they will NOT inflate the TypeScript percentage in the stats bar.
# Remove that line if you want .vl to show up in the stats under TypeScript.

*.vl linguist-language=TypeScript
*.vl linguist-detectable=false
